<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="2" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[264,1325,1148,1894]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,439,1308,1334]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Gorgoniids with variable branching patterns: pinnate, dichotomous, or filiform. Branch anastomosis absent; although occasionally present in two species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Hickson, 1904" authorityName="Hickson" authorityYear="1904" class="Anthozoa" family="Gorgoniidae" genus="Leptogorgia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Alcyonacea" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="gilchristi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">L. gilchristi</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hickson" box="[356,531,1388,1414]" pageId="1" pageNumber="10" refString="Hickson, S. J. (1904) The Alcyonaria of the Cape of Good Hope. Part II. Marine Investigations in South Africa, 3, 211 - 239." type="journal article" year="1904">
Hickson, 
<number box="[471,531,1388,1414]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="1904.0">1904</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Williams &amp; Lindo, 1997" authorityName="Williams &amp; Lindo" authorityYear="1997" box="[600,1011,1388,1414]" class="Anthozoa" family="Gorgoniidae" genus="Leptogorgia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Alcyonacea" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="bayeri">
<emphasis box="[600,707,1388,1413]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">L. bayeri</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Williams" box="[716,1011,1388,1414]" pageId="1" pageNumber="11" refString="Williams, G. C. &amp; Lindo, K. G. (1997) A review of the octocorallian genus Leptogorgia (Anthozoa: Gorgoniidae) in the Indian Ocean and Subantarctic, with description of a new species and comparisons with related taxa. Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, 49, 15, 499 - 521." type="journal article" year="1997">
Williams &amp; Lindo, 
<number box="[949,1011,1388,1414]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="1997.0">1997</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Axis horny, with a crosschambered central core containing a network of organic filaments frequently mineralized. Colonies with a simple or complex spreading holdfast, or without a holdfast and lying free on the sea floor. Coenenchymal sclerites are radiates and/or spindles, some with bent ends, with symmetrically or asymmetrically warty tuberculation. In some species, warts are fused into incomplete disks. Anthocodial sclerites usually flat rods and platelets. Colour variable: white, yellow, orange, red, violet, or brownish, and bicoloured (based on 
<bibRefCitation author="Williams" pageId="1" pageNumber="10" refString="Williams, G. C. (1992) The Alcyonacea of southern Africa. Gorgonian octocorals (Coelenterata, Anthozoa). Annals of the South African Museum, 101, 8, 181 - 296." type="journal article" year="1992">
Williams 
<number box="[328,390,1668,1694]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="1992.0">1992</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Williams" box="[402,688,1668,1694]" pageId="1" pageNumber="11" refString="Williams, G. C. &amp; Lindo, K. G. (1997) A review of the octocorallian genus Leptogorgia (Anthozoa: Gorgoniidae) in the Indian Ocean and Subantarctic, with description of a new species and comparisons with related taxa. Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, 49, 15, 499 - 521." type="journal article" year="1997">
Williams &amp; Lindo 
<number box="[626,688,1668,1694]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="1997.0">1997</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; Grasshoff 
<number box="[824,886,1668,1694]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="1988.0">1988</number>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Williams" box="[899,1210,1668,1694]" pageId="1" pageNumber="11" refString="Williams, G. C. &amp; Vennan, J. S. (2001) A revision of the Indo-West Pacific taxa of the gorgonian genus Pseudopterogorgia (Octocorallia: Gorgoniidae), with the description of a new species from western India. Bulletin of the Biological Society of Washington, 10, 71 - 95." type="journal article" year="2001">
Williams &amp; Vennam 
<number box="[1148,1210,1668,1694]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="2001.0">2001</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Bayer" pageId="1" pageNumber="10" refString="Bayer, F. M. &amp; Macintyre, I. G. (2001) The mineral component of the axis and holdfast of some gorgonacean octocorals (Coelenterata: Anthozoa), with special reference to the family Gorgoniidae. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington 114, 309 - 345." type="journal article" year="2001">
Bayer &amp; Macintyre 
<number box="[392,455,1708,1734]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="2001.0">2001</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="2" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="1.[264,1325,1148,1894]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,472,1748,1774]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Distribution.</emphasis>
Eastern Pacific (from southern California to 
<collectingCountry box="[1010,1078,1748,1774]" name="Chile" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Chile</collectingCountry>
); western and southern Africa; western 
<collectingCountry box="[521,626,1788,1814]" name="United States of America" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">America</collectingCountry>
; Caribbean Sea; Mediterranean Sea; south west Indian Ocean; and one subAntarctic species (
<bibRefCitation author="Verrill" box="[731,880,1828,1854]" pageId="1" pageNumber="10" refString="Verrill, A. E. (1868) Notes on Radiata in the Museum of Yale College, Number 6: Review of the corals and polyps of the West Coast of America. Transactions of the Connecticut Academy of Arts and Sciences, (Second Edition), 1, 377 - 422." type="journal article" year="1868">
Verrill 
<number box="[819,880,1828,1854]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="1868.187">1868</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Verrill" box="[897,959,1828,1854]" pageId="1" pageNumber="10" refString="Verrill, A. E. (1870) Notes on Radiata in the Museum of Yale College, Number 6: Review of the corals and polyps of the West Coast of America. Transactions of the Connecticut Academy of Arts and Sciences, (Second Edition), 1, 519 - 558." type="journal article" year="1870">1870</bibRefCitation>
; Grasshoff 
<number box="[1101,1240,1828,1854]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="1988.1992">1988, 1992</number>
, 
<number box="[1256,1318,1828,1854]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="1997.0">1997</number>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Williams" box="[264,548,1868,1894]" pageId="1" pageNumber="11" refString="Williams, G. C. &amp; Lindo, K. G. (1997) A review of the octocorallian genus Leptogorgia (Anthozoa: Gorgoniidae) in the Indian Ocean and Subantarctic, with description of a new species and comparisons with related taxa. Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, 49, 15, 499 - 521." type="journal article" year="1997">
Williams &amp; Lindo 
<number box="[485,548,1868,1894]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" value="1997.0">1997</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[264,1323,283,550]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,433,283,309]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Remarks.</emphasis>
The taxonomic status of the Indian Ocean species of the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[1179,1323,284,309]" class="Anthozoa" family="Gorgoniidae" genus="Leptogorgia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Alcyonacea" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1179,1323,284,309]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Leptogorgia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was thoroughly discussed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Williams" box="[635,976,324,350]" pageId="2" pageNumber="11" refString="Williams, G. C. &amp; Lindo, K. G. (1997) A review of the octocorallian genus Leptogorgia (Anthozoa: Gorgoniidae) in the Indian Ocean and Subantarctic, with description of a new species and comparisons with related taxa. Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, 49, 15, 499 - 521." type="journal article" year="1997">
Williams and Lindo (
<number box="[903,966,324,350]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="1997.0">1997</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation author="Williams" pageId="2" pageNumber="11" refString="Williams, G. C. &amp; Vennan, J. S. (2001) A revision of the Indo-West Pacific taxa of the gorgonian genus Pseudopterogorgia (Octocorallia: Gorgoniidae), with the description of a new species from western India. Bulletin of the Biological Society of Washington, 10, 71 - 95." type="journal article" year="2001">
Williams and Vennam (
<number box="[273,337,364,390]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="2001.0">2001</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Williams" box="[358,708,364,390]" pageId="2" pageNumber="11" refString="Williams, G. C. &amp; Vennan, J. S. (2001) A revision of the Indo-West Pacific taxa of the gorgonian genus Pseudopterogorgia (Octocorallia: Gorgoniidae), with the description of a new species from western India. Bulletin of the Biological Society of Washington, 10, 71 - 95." type="journal article" year="2001">
Williams and Vennam (
<number box="[639,700,364,390]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="2001.0">2001</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
decided to transfer these species of 
<taxonomicName box="[1147,1291,364,389]" class="Anthozoa" family="Gorgoniidae" genus="Leptogorgia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Alcyonacea" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1147,1291,364,389]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Leptogorgia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Kukenthal, 1919" authorityName="Kukenthal" authorityYear="1919" box="[401,858,403,430]" class="Anthozoa" family="Gorgoniidae" genus="Pseudopterogorgia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Alcyonacea" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[401,625,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Pseudopterogorgia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kukenthal" box="[642,858,403,430]" pageId="2" pageNumber="10" refString="Kukenthal, W. (1919). Gorgonaria. Wissenschaftliche Ergebnisse der Deutschen Tiefsee-Expedition auf der Dampfer Valdivia 1898 - 1899, 13, 2, 1 - 946." type="journal article" year="1919">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[642,775,403,429]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Kükenthal</emphasis>
, 
<number box="[799,858,404,430]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="1919.0">1919</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
mainly based on the occurrence of scaphoid­like sclerites in the coenenchyme; consequently the distribution of 
<taxonomicName box="[1179,1323,444,469]" class="Anthozoa" family="Gorgoniidae" genus="Leptogorgia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Alcyonacea" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1179,1323,444,469]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Leptogorgia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the Indian Ocean could be invalid. However, more taxonomic research is needed before a zoogeographical pattern can be established.
</paragraph>
